 the bracken DB); whereas the `-l ` flag should be the read length, which depends on the reads you want to use the DB on, therefore they supply multiple options.\n\nSo finally one can conclude, that the files in this DB are wrongly labelled `database50mers.kmer_distrib` should be `database50readlenght.kmer_distrib` IMYO; but I will double-check with @jenniferlu717 to be sure. (See https://github.com/jenniferlu717/Bracken/issues/249)\n\nHowever, the arguments in Galaxy do use the correct wording, i.e. `Read length` in the DM does indeed choose the matching DB from the prebuilt DB.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1709285002,"nonce":"5Z4VOLMiUoUZ/svTBDADUskGRJ8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s51ltms","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5745#issuecomment-1972820396"},"message":"See: https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/5804","files":null}]}